Name: Identicals
Cast: Tim Faraday, Nora-Jane Noone, Tony Way
Synopsis: None Of Us Are As Unique As We Think. Identicals is a highly unconventional romantic thriller: an obsessive love story stripped down and re-arranged into the looping logic of a nightmare.

Name: Outlander
Cast: James Caviezel, Sophia Myles, Jack Huston
Synopsis: A time traveler arrives in ancient Norway only to bring horror and death with him in the form of an alien monster intent on killing everyone in its path.

Name: Scandalize My Name
Cast: Morgan Freeman, Harry Belafonte, Ossie Davis
Synopsis: This potent documentary, narrated by Morgan Freeman, examines several prominent African-American performers in the American film and television industries during the 1950s Communist witch-hunting McCarthy era.

Name: Ruth - Justice Ginsburg In Her Own Words
Cast: Ruth Bader Ginsburg, Barack Obama, Joe Biden
Synopsis: How does someone with three strikes against her, rise to the highest court in the land, the U. S. Supreme Court?

Name: Starz Inside: Bloodsucking Cinema
Cast: John Carpenter, Leonard Maltin, Cheech Marin
Synopsis: The hypnotic attraction that only a stake or sunlight can defeat! The history of vampire films is explored via interviews and clips from Interview With A Vampire, The Lost Boys, Dracula, etc. A Starz Originals production.

Name: When We Speak
Cast: Rose McGowan, Katharine Gun, Helen Evans
Synopsis: British intelligence employee Katharine Gun, Oxfam aid worker Helen Evans and Hollywood actress Rose McGowan open the lid on what happens to women whistleblowers in When We Speak.

Name: Cutting Edge: The Magic of Movie Editing
Cast: Kathy Bates, James Cameron, George Lucas
Synopsis: Top-flight Hollywood film editors reveal the secrets of the trade and how editing can make or break a movie. Film clips, interviews, and a unique hands-on session highlight the magic in this Starz Original production.

Name: Midnight Movies
Cast: John Waters, David Lynch, George A. Romero
Synopsis: The history of 6 landmark cult films - "The Rocky Horror Picture Show", "Eraserhead", "Pink Flamingos", "Night Of The Living Dead" and more - is told through clips and director interviews. A Starz Originals Production.

Name: Barbara Lee: Speaking Truth to Power
Cast: Barbara Lee, Cory Booker, John Lewis
Synopsis: Paints a vivid and timely portrait of Congresswoman Barbara Lee, a steadfast voice for human rights, peace, and diplomacy in the U.S. Government.

Name: Lonesome Dove Church
Cast: Tom Berenger, Greyston Holt, Alex Zahara
Synopsis: A Texas preacher who dreams of building his own church puts his life on the line to save his son, an accused outlaw.

Name: Sierra
Cast: Wanda Hendrix, Audie Murphy, Dean Jagger
Synopsis: A tomboy frontier lawyer finds an outlaw and his son hiding out from a false charge of murder.

Name: The Warrior's Way
Cast: Kate Bosworth, Geoffrey Rush, Danny Huston
Synopsis: A fugitive assassin travels from the Far East to the Wild West, where he hides in a small town in the American badlands. While there, he teams up with a seasoned fighter and a circus-knife-thrower to settle old scores.

Name: The Shakiest Gun in the West
Cast: Don Knotts, Barbara Rhoades, Jackie Coogan
Synopsis: Dentist leaves sedate, early 19th century Pennsylvania to set up practice on the western frontier. En route he gets involved with a lady bandit, turned federal agent, who's on a dangerous mission.

Name: Rooster Cogburn
Cast: John Wayne, Katharine Hepburn, Anthony Zerbe
Synopsis: The one-eyed, tough-as-nails lawman with "true grit" teams with a Bible-thumping spinster schoolmarm to bring the killers of her father to justice - and recover a load of explosive nitro in this action-comedy-western.

Name: Santa Fe
Cast: Randolph Scott, Janis Carter, Jerome Courtland
Synopsis: After the Civil War, two brothers, once the best of friends, try to reconcile their differences that led them to fight on opposite sides in this stirring, emotional Western.

Name: The Great Northfield Minnesota Raid
Cast: Cliff Robertson, Robert Duvall, Luke Askew
Synopsis: The gangs of Jesse James and Cole Younger join forces for a bungled robbery of the bank in Northfield, Minnesota.

Name: Lonely Are The Brave
Cast: Kirk Douglas, Gena Rowlands, Walter Matthau
Synopsis: A free-spirit cowboy escapes from jail and heads out on horseback for the mountains - but this is a new age, and the law uses modern technology in their manhunt.

Name: Out of Liberty
Cast: Jasen Wade, Brandon Ray Olive, Casey Elliott
Synopsis: In the winter of 1839, a jailer is tasked with overseeing Missouri's most wanted men as they await trial.

Name: Ten Wanted Men
Cast: Randolph Scott, Richard Boone, Jocelyn Brando
Synopsis: Rival cattle ranchers become mortal enemies when a young woman seeks refuge with one man because she doesn't love the other - the spurned rancher hires ten gunslingers and proceeds to wreak havoc.

Name: The Stranger Wore a Gun
Cast: Randolph Scott, Claire Trevor, Joan Weldon
Synopsis: A man whose life is saved by a bandit reluctantly joins in a conspiracy to loot the stage lines - and things get hairy when he decides to go straight.

Name: Winchester '73
Cast: James Stewart, Shelley Winters, Dan Duryea
Synopsis: Lin McAdam wins a sharp-shooting contest and claims a Winchester rifle as a prize. When Dutch sneaks into McAdam's room and steals the weapon, McAdam chases Dutch across the state and toward an epic confrontation.

Name: Butch And Sundance: The Early Days
Cast: William Katt, Tom Berenger, Jill Eikenberry
Synopsis: "Prequel" to the classic Newman-Redford western recounts the legend of the outlaw pair's meeting. Directed by Richard Lester ("Superman II", "A Hard Day's Night").

Name: Dead Birds
Cast: Henry Thomas, Patrick Fugit, Mark Boone Junior
Synopsis: After robbing a bank, a group of Confederate soldiers hole up in an abandoned plantation and soon find themselves at the mercy of supernatural forces.

Name: Gunfight in Abilene
Cast: Bobby Darin, Emily Banks, Leslie Nielsen
Synopsis: A sheriff, haunted by the accidental killing of his best friend, refuses to wear a gun. But when the brother of his best friend is murdered, the lawman must make a choice.

Name: The Duel
Cast: Liam Hemsworth, Alice Braga, Emory Cohen
Synopsis: A Texas Ranger investigates a series of murders in an Old West town that's run by a former Confederate officer.

Name: Drums Across The River
Cast: Audie Murphy, Walter Brennan, Lyle Bettger
Synopsis: When white men hunger after the gold on Ute Native American land, a bigoted young man finds himself forced into a peacekeeping role.

Name: Ned Kelly
Cast: Orlando Bloom, Heath Ledger, Naomi Watts
Synopsis: A clever outlaw leads his gang on a crime spree throughout 19th c. Australia to avenge the wrongful imprisonment of his mother and closest friends.

Name: Cowgirls n' Angels
Cast: Bailee Madison, James Cromwell, Alicia Witt
Synopsis: A spunky twelve-year-old girl sets her sights on joining a team of female rodeo trick-riders - but first she must convince her mom that she's doing the right thing.

Name: The Doolins Of Oklahoma
Cast: Randolph Scott, George Macready, Louise Allbritton
Synopsis: When his former gang forces him to resume leadership, Bill Doolin, trying to go straight, walks into lawmen's guns rather than risk bringing further unhappiness to his wife.

Name: The Tall T
Cast: Randolph Scott, Richard Boone, Maureen O'Sullivan
Synopsis: An unlucky cowboy finds himself on a stage hijacked by an outlaw and his men, and things get worse when the crooks hold one of the passengers - a mine owner's daughter - for ransom.

Name: The Last Sunset
Cast: Rock Hudson, Kirk Douglas, Dorothy Malone
Synopsis: Two enemies - a short-tempered outlaw and a haunted sheriff - find themselves working together on a cattle drive, with both trying to outwit the other in this intense story.

Name: Gold
Cast: Nina Hoss, Marko Mandic, Peter Kurth
Synopsis: When British Columbia erupts in gold, a group of Germans travel to North America to claim a piece of the prize.

Name: The Battle at Apache Pass
Cast: John Lund, Jeff Chandler, Susan Cabot
Synopsis: When Cochise bands together with Geronimo and other Native American tribes, Major Colton abandons his fort, heading towards Fort Sheridan, through Apache Pass.

Name: The Lawless Breed
Cast: Rock Hudson, Julia Adams, John McIntire
Synopsis: After being released from prison, former gun-fighter John Wesley Hardin hopes to have his autobiography published in order to rehabilitate his tarnished reputation.

Name: Stars Over Texas
Cast: Eddie Dean, Roscoe Ates, Shirley Patterson
Synopsis: A cowhand exploits his uncanny resemblance to a ranch's endangered foreman to help corral a gang of thievin' cattle rustlers.

Name: The Proud Rebel
Cast: Alan Ladd, Olivia de Havilland, Dean Jagger
Synopsis: While on a search for a doctor, a Confederate veteran must help a small town woman save her ranch in return for her saving him from facing jail time.

Name: Black Fox
Cast: Christopher Reeve, Tony Todd, Raoul Trujillo
Synopsis: Two men - one white, the other Black, and as close as natural brothers - risk everything when they agree to negotiate with Indians who kidnapped women and children during a violent raid in Civil War Texas.
